aweme_info.desc: Did you know you can cast your iPhone to a raspberry pi? You can achieve this by installing RPiPlay - An open-source implementation of an AirPlay mirroring server for the Raspberry Pi. The easiest way of installing RPiPlay is through PiKISS, which is effectively, a collection of a bunch of install scripts with a user friendly menu. RPiPlay can be found under the “others” option. Now, you can run RPiPlay from the “ System Tools“, section in the menu. Once you run the application, a new airplay device should become discoverable. Just click on it to cast your screen. Your device should now be transmitting both video and audio to your raspberry pi. It is worth noting that the stream quality is not always the best but If you ever need to cast your iPhone , iPad or Macbook onto a larger monitor in a pinch, this might just do the trick. original_client_text.markup_text:
Did you know you can cast your iPhone to a raspberry pi?

You can achieve this by installing RPiPlay - An open-source implementation of an AirPlay mirroring server for the Raspberry Pi.

The easiest way of installing RPiPlay is through PiKISS, which is effectively, a collection of a bunch of install scripts with a user friendly menu. RPiPlay can be found under the “others” option.

Now, you can run RPiPlay from the “ System Tools“, section in the menu. Once you run the application, a new airplay device should become discoverable. Just click on it to cast your screen.

Your device should now be transmitting both video and audio to your raspberry pi.

It is worth noting that the stream quality is not always the best but If you ever need to cast your iPhone , iPad or Macbook onto a larger monitor in a pinch, this might just do the trick.
